21/11/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and visiting Macedonian counterpart Nikola Gruevski reiterated on Monday (November 20th) their countries' common hope of joining NATO in 2008. 
Both said they expected next week's summit in Riga to result in clear messages regarding eventual membership invitations. 
Gruevski's visit also focused on economic co-operation and EU membership talks.
In other news Monday, Macedonian Foreign Minister Antonio Milososki met with EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn in Brussels. 
Rehn says he stressed the need for continued reforms in Macedonia, particularly in the areas of judicial reform and the fight against corruption and crime, if the country wants to get a date for starting accession talks. 
(Vjesnik, Vecer - 21/11/06; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, HINA, AFX - 20/11/06)
